==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Finback
<hw>Fin"back`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any whale of the genera <gen>Sibbaldius</gen>,
<gen>Bal⟦ae⟧noptera</gen>, and allied genera, of the family
<fam>Bal⟦ae⟧nopterid⟦ae⟧</fam>, characterized by a prominent fin on the
back. The common finbacks of the New England coast are <spn>Sibbaldius
tectirostris</spn> and <spn>S. tuberosus</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

